				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Ok, something I have never understood, is how the Tiny Cloak of Darkest Night kept casters happy? Can someone enlighten me? </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Our invis song is a group invis and when its sung in group with any pet class it kills their pet or breaks their charm.  This more than anything else may be why some chanters hate us. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-14.gif" border="0" alt="Devil" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
The Gobbey ring sucks imo.  I worked with it for a bit but I found it to be more trouble than its worth as it requires that  you are targeted when its cast.  I just went back to using our invis song and perfected my timing.   Sell the bloody thing for 20k and buy yourself a pretty.
<br />

<br />
Now the Tiny Cloak is one of my most treasured possesions and I don't really solo any more.  I use it daily and particularly in those runs to the outer GoD zones.  It's one of those items that you will use more than you ever thought you would.
<br />
