			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Goblin Gazughi Ring vs. Tiny Cloak of Darkest Night<a name="55444"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 04 11:42 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The Goblin Ring has virtually no use except to inta-cast break charm when charm kiting / swarming.  Period.  I use my Tiny Cloak EVERY single day I play (it's utility is now a part of me), but the ONLY time I use it during a swarm kite is if I've accidentally forgotten to equip my Goblin Ring for charm break.  At that point, I click the Tiny Cloak (before pet dies to swarm), equip my Goblin Ring, and then finish off chanting down my ex-pet.  It's likely that I will have 20%+ ex-pet HPs to chant down because of this mistake.
<br />

<br />
This whole discussion really boils down to how effecient you want to be while charm kiting / swarming.  I shoot for breaking charm at between 10% and 20% HPs left on pet.  In my experience, if you try for anything less than this (unless your swarm is thin enough by then to have lower dps that's easier to guage), you run the risk of losing a lot of pets.  Invis song may work, but it is very inefficient for guaging the 10-20% window for charm break.  Tiny Cloak is better (1.5 cast time), but Inst-Click absolutely RULES for efficiently timed charm-breaking.
<br />

<br />
With the target toggling key functionality added with the new target cycling functionality, the added price of having to target yourself for using the Goblin Ring is really not a high price at all anymore.  Yes, Mosquito Boots would be better, but you make do with what you have until an upgrade comes along.
<br />

<br />
My opinion remains unchanged here.  Use the Goblin Ring for Charm Kiting / Swarming.  Use the Tiny Cloak for everything else (that you need utility self-only invis for).
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
