				<td colspan="2"><span>The cloak is a definite winner for the utility of invis. Quite handy for pulling in many zones too, its such a fast cast time.
<br />

<br />
The ring - well, I don't have one but when I swarm kite with the cloak I can generally break charm at 10-15% reasonably reliably. I like not having to self-target as it lets me keep both my pet and my pet's previous target buffered, though this isn't essential.
<br />

<br />
Sure, the instant-invis break is a bonus, but really the mosquito boots are far superior for this if you find charm-break timing a problem. Personally I find the cloak perfectly adequate for all but the really large swarms, its going to depend on you though as to how much you swarm, how easy you find it to time breaks etc.</span></td>
